flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Scheduled run (daily) and on-demand when demand/schedule variance exceeds threshold (X%) or bottleneck flag raised by line telemetry.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers + STREAMS - Consolidate inputs]
  N1 --> N2[Stream: Cortex Auto Forecast + STREAMS - Forecast & capacity modeling]
  N2 --> N3{PB: Process Builder (Process - Rules - Remote Functions) - Run allocation optimizer}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[PB: Remote Functions (Transaction) - Commit allocations]
  N4 --> N5[PB: Process Builder (Notification) - Notify operations]
  N5 --> N6[PB: UI Screens (dashboard & CWB lifecycle) - Surface results & allow override]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Reduced COGS and downtime through targeted bottleneck resolution, improved line throughput and takt compliance, better alignment of capacity with demand forecasts, and auditable writeback to ERP.]
  N3 -->|Available capacity required capacit...| B1[Invoke bottleneck-driven subprocess (Process Builder Subprocess + Remote Functions) to reprioritize orders, suggest overtime, machine swaps, or transfer to alternate sites.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Revised allocation plan with feasible trade-offs or escalation to supply chain/planning for manual intervention.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Skill/certification mismatch for allo...| B2[Create Action Item and CWB entry to route to planners with suggested alternatives (retraining, swap, temporary contractor) and optional manual override.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Allocation paused for planner decision; system logs recommendation and timestamps override decisions for audit.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|ERP writeback failure or transaction ...| B3[Rollback Transaction node in Process Builder, persist allocation snapshot in Subject Areas, notify IT and planners, and schedule automated retry.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Allocations staged pending resolution; no partial commits in ERP; stakeholders alerted for remediation.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]